source.Name: Total population
source.Summary: Population: Total population and distribution by age and sex estimated to be consistent with the population by age and sex of the (a) 1950, 1960, 1970, 1980, 1997, 2007, 2017 censuses; (b) adjusted for under/over count; (c) adjusted for age heaping; (d) adjusted for under enumeration of children under age 15; (e) official estimates through 2022; and with estimates of the subsequent trends in fertility, mortality and international migration. In addition, the 1997, 2003, 2011 DHS and 2008 MICS and 2009 AIS and 2018 MIS survey estimates have been considered.

source.Name: Total fertility rate
source.Summary: Fertility: Total fertility rate and age pattern of fertility based on: (a) official estimates of age-specific fertility rates through 2013; (b) registered births classified by age of mother and the underlying female population by age through 2019; (c) birth-histories data from the 1997, 2003, 2011, 2022-2023 DHS and 2008 MICS and 2015 AIS and 2018 MIS; (d) births in the household in the preceding 12 (or 24) months classified by age of mother from the 1970, 1980, 1997, 2007 censuses; (e) indirect estimates obtained from the application of the reverse survival method to the 1950, 1960, 1970, 1980, 1997, 2007, 2017 censuses and 2009 AIS; (f) indirect estimates obtained from stable population assumption; (g) cohort-completed fertility backdated by the mean age of childbearing from the 1950, 1980, 1997, 2007, 2017 censuses and 1997, 2003, 2011 DHS and 2008 MICS and 2009 AIS and 2018 MIS. In addition, the births in the household in the preceding 12 (or 24) months classified by age of mother from the 2017 Census have been considered.

source.Name: Life expectancy at birth
source.Summary: Overall Mortality: Life expectancy at birth and age pattern of mortality based on: (a) registered deaths by age and sex available through 2021; (b) The demographic impact of AIDS has been factored into the mortality estimates; (c) estimates using HIV/AIDS model life tables and estimates of under-five mortality (5q0) and adult mortality (45q15) with UNAIDS estimates of adult HIV prevalence, and ART coverage for children and adults. Mortality rates for Spectrum were calculated by removing AIM's estimates of HIV-related mortality from all-cause mortality rate estimates published in the 2024 revision of the World Population Prospects.

source.Name: Age Mortality
source.Summary: Adult and Old Age Mortality: Estimates derived from: (a) recent household deaths data by age and sex from the 1997, 2007, 2017 censuses and 2019-2020 MZ-SRS; (b) recent household deaths adjusted at adult ages for underregistration using death distribution methods; (c) siblings deaths from the 2008 MICS and 2011 DHS; (d) maternal orphanhood from the 1997, 2007 censuses and 1997, 2003, 2011 DHS and 2008 MICS and 2009 AIS; (e) paternal orphanhood from the 1997, 2003, 2011 DHS and 2007 Census and 2008 MICS and 2009 AIS; (f) indirect estimates of male adult mortality based on female widowhood data from the 1970, 1980, 1997, 2007, 2017 censuses and 1997, 2011 DHS and 2008 MICS and 2009, 2015 AIS; (g) intercensal survivorship from successive census age distributions; (h) estimates of under-five, adult and old age mortality. In addition, the (a) siblings deaths from the 1997, 2003 DHS; (b) indirect estimates of male adult mortality based on female widowhood data from the 1960 Census have been considered.

source.Name: Infant/child mortality
source.Summary: Child Mortality: Under-five mortality based on: (a) direct estimates from births and deaths under-five calculated from full birth histories data from the 2003, 2011 DHS and 2008 MICS; (b) indirect estimates from data on children ever born and surviving from the 1980, 1997, 2007, 2017 censuses and 1991 NDS and 1995 MICS and 2009, 2015 AIS and 2018 MIS; (c) International estimates used up to 2021. In addition, the (a) registered infant and child deaths through 2021; (b) direct estimates from births and deaths under-five calculated from full birth histories data from the 1997 DHS; (c) indirect estimates from data on children ever born and surviving from the 1950, 1970 censuses; (d) recent household deaths from the 1997, 2007, 2017 censuses and 2019-2021 MZ-SRS have been considered.

source.Name: International migration
source.Summary: Migration: International migration based on: (a) information on foreign-born populations from censuses and registers from major countries of destination; (b) information on the number of migrant workers or about labor migration (in South Africa); (c) estimates derived as the differences between overall population growth and natural increase; (d) UNHCR statistics on the number of refugees in the main countries of asylum.
